VIRONMENTAL RECORD CENTRES: A DECADE OF PROGRESS?.IN 1977, THE MUSEUMS ASSOCIATION CONVENED A STANDING COMMITTEE ONENVIRONMENTAL RECORD CENTRES. DESCRIBES THE WORK OF THE COMMITTEE, ANDPRESENTS A RESUME OF THE CURRENT STATE OF ENVIRONMENTAL RECORDING IN THE UK.IT INCLUDES COVERAGE OF WORK WITHIN 6 MAIN SUBJECT GROUPS (ARCHAEOLOGY,GEOLOGY, HISTORIC BUILDINGS, SOCIAL HISTORY, INDUSTRIAL HISTORY AND BIOLOGY)